1
00:00:06,130 --> 00:00:09,520
Well, here we are. I turn down here
at the next block.

2
00:00:09,570 --> 00:00:13,500
Thanks, mister. I'll get off there.

3
00:00:18,350 --> 00:00:21,160
- Want anything else?
- No.

4
00:00:21,210 --> 00:00:23,710
Hey, you!

5
00:00:25,420 --> 00:00:29,240
- Me?
- Yeah you. Where re you heading?

6
00:00:29,290 --> 00:00:30,520
East.

7
00:00:30,570 --> 00:00:35,300
Too bad. I thought if you was heading north
I might be able to help you out.

8
00:00:35,350 --> 00:00:38,120
I m pushing myself late tonight.
I don t like to ride alone at night.

9
00:00:38,170 --> 00:00:42,470
I am one of those guys who gotta talk
or I fall asleep.

10
00:00:42,520 --> 00:00:45,000
My partner, he s got Lou to keep him company, but ...

11
00:00:45,050 --> 00:00:46,850
... I ain t got nobody at all.

12
00:00:46,900 --> 00:00:49,290
- Where re you coming from?
- West.

13
00:00:49,340 --> 00:00:50,700
Yeah sure, I know, but ...

14
00:00:50,750 --> 00:00:52,130
... where? LA?

15
00:00:52,180 --> 00:00:54,590
- Maybe.
- I ve got a cousin out in LA ...

16
00:00:54,640 --> 00:00:57,840
- You don t say.
- Yeah. He s been out ...

17
00:00:57,890 --> 00:00:59,250
You're not much of a talker, are you?

18
00:00:59,300 --> 00:01:01,240
My mother taught me never to speak
to strangers.

19
00:01:01,290 --> 00:01:03,170
- Oh, wise guy is it.
- So what!?

20
00:01:03,220 --> 00:01:05,320
Okay, okay. Don t get sore.

21
00:01:05,370 --> 00:01:08,650
Trying to be sociable. That s all.

22
00:01:08,700 --> 00:01:10,350
Hey, Grandma!

23
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:14,440
Give me change for a dime, will you?.

24
00:01:21,610 --> 00:01:24,450
Let s have something quieter this time, Joe.
My head s splitting.

25
00:01:24,500 --> 00:01:28,100
It that what's wrong with it?

26
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Done with your coffee?

